WHEN Isaac Mashego (37) heard a taxi driver throwing a passenger out of his vehicle he ignored it.He and his best friend Jack Mothapo (33) had a few drinks after finishing their piece job in Centurion, Tshwane and Isaac fell asleep in the taxi on the way home to Soshanguve, north of Tshwane.Little did he know it was Jack who had been thrown out of the taxi. And now Jack is missing!His brother, Mokhureng Mothapo (47), said his family last saw Jack on 29 January when he left for work.&ldquo;Isaac came to my home at about 8.30pm that night saying that Jack was dropped off on the Mabopane Highway and he did not know where he was,&rdquo; he said. Isaac told him that his brother was dropped off on the highway because he did not want to pay for his taxi fare.Mokhureng said that he blamed Isaac for not paying Jack&rsquo;s taxi fare.&ldquo;I would have paid him back when they got home,&rdquo; he said.Isaac told Daily Sun that he and his friend got paid R200 each.&ldquo;I was surprised when I woke up and tried to talk to my friend, who was sitting in the seat in front of me, but there was no response,&rdquo; he said.That&rsquo;s when he was told that his friend was thrown out because he refused to pay.&ldquo;If I&rsquo;d known earlier that it was him I would have paid for him.&rdquo;Soshanguve police spokeswoman Sergeant Catherine Makhubela said a missing person&rsquo;s case was opened.